Example 1: Hello World Program
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
int main() {
    cout << "Hello, World!";
    return 0;
}
Output

Hello, World!
Every C++ program starts from the main() function.

The cout is the standard output stream which
 prints the Hello, World! string on the monitor.

The return 0; is the Exit status of the program.

Example 2: Hello World Program
#include <iostream>
int main() {
    std::cout << "Hello, World!";
    return 0;
}
Output

Hello, World!
